-- China Considers Moving to `Sound' Monetary Policy, Business News Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-01T23:17:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/china-may-change-to-sound-monetary-policy-business-news-says.html
China is considering changing to a
“sound” monetary policy from a “moderately loose” one next
year, China Business News reported today, citing two
unidentified people.  The government will likely maintain a “proactive” fiscal
policy, the report said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
